do%20is%20have%20an%20outburst%20during%20the%20eclipse%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20decades-old%20mystery%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAstronomers%20aren't%20sure%20exactly%20why%20Comet%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%2C%20which%20orbits%20the%20sun%20every%2071%20years%2C%20has%20brightened%20so%20drastically%20in%20recent%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiles%20said%20there%20may%20be%20an%20active%20ice%20volcano%20on%20the%20surface%20that%20is%20causing%20it%20to%20light%20up%20the%20sky.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20of%20a%20revolutionary%20idea%20that%20you%20have%20liquid%20inside%20a%20comet%20and%20scientists%20have%20for%20decades%20never%20really%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20see%20this%20comet%20do%20what%20it's%20doing%2C%20you%20can't%20really%20explain%20it%20without%20saying%20'As%20well%20as%20solids%20and%20gases%2C%20there%20are%20liquids%20inside%20the%20comet%20making%20it%20behave%20in%20this%20very%20unusual%20way%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20helps%20back%20up%20a%20theory%20that%20comets%20not%20only%20brought%20water%20to%20Earth%20but%20also%20helped%20spread%20the%20germs%20of%20life%20on%20our%20planet%2C%20Miles%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BComets%20come%20from%20the%20Oort%20cloud%20which%20is%20far%20beyond%20the%20orbit%20of%20Neptune%20and%20Uranus%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Edward%20Gomez%20of%20the%20Las%20Cumbres%20Observatory%20in%20Cardiff%2C%20Wales%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20the%20stuff%20which%20is%20left%20over%20from%20when%20the%20solar%20system%20was%20made.%20Everything%20that%20formed%20into%20planets%20has%20been%20evolving%20for%204.5%20Billion%20years%20(e.g.%20through%20geophysical%20processes%20and%20weather)%20but%20the%20Oort%20cloud%20is%20pristine.%20It%20gives%20us%20a%20great%20snapshot%20of%20what%20conditions%20were%20like%20when%20the%20planets%20formed%20and%20how%20the%20planets%20formed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221689%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Comet%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%2C%20which%20was%20first%20spotted%20in%201812%20and%20orbits%20the%20sun%20every%2071%20years%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c25e379440b70019270e74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22844%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EComet%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%20was%20first%20spotted%20in%201812%20and%20orbits%20the%20sun%20every%2071%20years%3Cp%3EComet%20Chasers%2FFaulkes%20Telescope%20Project%2FLas%20Cumbres%20Observatory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EComet%2012P%2FPons-Brooks'%20outburst%20was%20discovered%20on%20July%2020%20by%20Elek%20Tam%C3%A1s%20of%20Harsona%20Observatory%2C%20Nyiregyhaza%2C%20Hungary%2C%20and%20was%20later%20captured%20by%20the%20Comet%20Chasers%2C%20a%20team%20of%20researchers%20led%20by%20Helen%20Usher%20of%20Cardiff%20University%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20using%20the%20Faulkes%20Telescope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20comet%20has%20likely%20streamed%2010%20billion%20kilograms%20of%20dust%20and%20ice%20into%20space%2C%20according%20to%20Carrie%20Holt%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%2C%20speaking%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fa-comet-has-sprouted-icy-wings-on-a-plunge-around-the-sun%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScientific%20American.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20people%20will%20have%20to%20wait%20until%20next%20year%20to%20see%20the%20comet%2C%20amateur%20astronomers%20could%20be%20in%20with%20a%20chance%20of%20seeing%20it%20now%20using%20a%20six-inch%20telescope%20and%20pointing%20it%20to%20the%20constellation%20of%20Draco%20in%20the%20Northern%20Sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20moment%20it%20is%20only%20really%20visible%20with%20a%20telescope%20at%20a%20nice%20dark%20site%20but%20around%20the%20time%20of%20the%20eclipse%20next%20April%2C%20it%20will%20be%