te-attack-wrestling-federation-chief-brij-bhushan-sharan-singh-4245570%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-embarrassment-on-my-face-despite-attack-wrestling-federation-chief-brij-bhushan-sharan-singh-4245570%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Improves%20Visa%20Wait%20Times%20For%20Indians%2C%20Yet%20To%20Recover%20Tourist%20Traffic%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETourism%20has%20bounced%20back%20furiously%20in%20the%20world's%20major%20tourism%20markets.%20Spain%20recovered%2086%25%20of%20its%20pre-pandemic%20tourist%20arrivals%20in%202022%2C%20and%20arrivals%20this%20year%20already%20show%20a%2028%25%20increase%20over%202019%20levels.%20France%20follows%20closely%20with%20year-to-date%20international%20visitors%20numbering%20just%203%25%20less%20than%20before%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20and%20their%20spending%20at%20record%20levels%2C%20according%20to%20Atout%20France%2C%20a%20government%20tourism%20agency.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20falling%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternational%20tourist%20arrivals%20remain%20at%2026%25%20below%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20according%20to%20a%20June%202023%20monthly%20report%20from%20the%20US%20Travel%20Association%2C%20with%20spending%20slower%2C%20too.%20At%20the%20close%20of%202022%2C%20international%20visitor%20spending%20in%20the%20US%20was%20at%20%2499%20billion%2C%20just%20over%2050%25%20of%20where%20it%20stood%20in%202019.%20That's%20a%20far%20cry%20from%202019%2C%20when%20the%20US%20received%2079.4%20million%20visitors%2C%20who%20spent%20%24181%20billion.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lag%20is%20very%20significant%2C%20and%20we%20are%20very%20concerned%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Geoff%20Freeman%2C%20US%20Travel's%20chief%20executive%20officer.%20%26quot%3BWe%20estimate%20that%20this%20year%20alone%20we're%20going%20to%20lose%20about%202.6%20million%20international%20visitors%20and%20%247%20billion%20less%20in%20spending.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20travel%20industry%20isn't%20expected%20to%20recover%20to%202019%20levels%20until%202025.%20Those%20two%20additional%20years%20will%20translate%20into%20%26quot%3Bbillions%20of%20dollars%20of%20lost%20spending%2C%20of%20lost%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Freeman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20history%2C%20the%20US%20is%20also%20running%20a%20multiyear%20travel%20deficit%3A%20Americans%20are%20spending%20more%20money%20abroad%20on%20their%20travels%20than%20international%20tourists%20are%20spending%20in%20the%20US.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBureaucracy%20and%20delays%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20Department's%20US%20visa%20processing%20delays%20continue%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20obstacle%20list.%20As%20of%20early%20July%2C%20visa%20wait%20times%20remained%20above%20400%20days%20for%20first-time%20applicants%20from%20top%20markets%20that%20do%20not%20qualify%20for%20visa%20waivers%2C%20according%20to%20US%20Travel.%20In%202019%2C%20travelers%20requiring%20visas%20to%20enter%20the%20US%20made%20up%2043%25%20of%20all%20inbound%20international%20travel.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20wait%20times%20are%20completely%20unacceptable%2C%20and%20they%20are%20discouraging%20travelers%20from%20coming%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Freeman.%20The%20government%20has%20been%20willing%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20problem%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20and%20improvements%20have%20been%20made%20with%20applicants%20from%20India%20and%20Brazil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20State%20Department%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%20that%20the%20agency%20was%20%26quot%3Bquickly%20lowering%20visitor%20visa%20interview%20wait%20times%20worldwide.%20In%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%20fiscal%20year%202023%20(through%20June%202023)%2C%20globally%20we%20issued%2019.4%25%20more%20nonimmigrant%20visas%20than%20we%20did%20during%20the%20same%20period%20in%20fiscal%20year%202019.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20median%20global%20interview%20appointment%20waiting%20time%20for%20visitor%20visas%20as%20of%20July%201%20was%20approximately%20three%20months%2C%20down%20about%20a%20third%20from%20%C2%A0120%20days%20in%20October%2C%20said%20the%20spokesperson%2C%20who%20added%20that%20additional%20officers%20heading%20overseas%20should%20match%20the%20State%20Department's%20global%20pre-pandemic%20staffing%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20destination%20rivals%20including%20Canada%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20EU%20are%20growing%20more%20aggressive%20in%20soliciting%20tourism%20and%20making%20themselves%20more%20accessible%20to%20such%20top%20US%20markets%20as%20Mexico%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Colombia%2C%20Argentina%2C%20Israel%20and%20Venezuela.%20Citizens%20from%20those%20countries%20can%20travel%20visa-free%20to%20the%20EU%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20while%20the%20UK%20has%20waived%20visa%20requirements%20for%20Colombia%20and%20Peru%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20waiting%20times%20for%20visas%2C%20US%20travel%20industry%20problems%20include%20hotel%20rates%20that%20have%20remained%20high%20since%20travel%20recommenced.%20Those%20prices%20are%20deterring%20international%20travelers%20who%20are%20concerned%20with%20high%20travel%20costs%2C%20a%20strong%20dollar%20and%20inflation%3B%20hotel%20demand%20in%20the%20US%20dipped%202%25%20in%20May%202023%2C%20data%20from%20US%20Travel%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETravelers%20are%20also%20dealing%20with%20delays%20getting%20through%20customs%20at%20airports%20and%20TSA%20wait%20times%20continue%20to%20increase.%20Bloomberg%20reached%20out%20to%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20but%20did%20not%20receive%20a%20response%20in%20time%20for%20publication.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20and%20on%2C%20across%20the%20board%2C%20we%20demonstrate%20that%20we%20don't%20prioritize%20travel%20the%20way%20that%20other%20markets%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20US%20Travel's%20Freeman.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20something%20that%20we%20have%20taken%20for%20granted%20here%20in%20the%20US%20for%20too%20long.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20leisure%20tourists%2C%20business%20travelers%20are%20being%20deterred%20by%20bureaucracy.%20Trade%20show%20exhibitors%20confirm%20that%20attendance%20is%20down%2020%25%2C%20says%20Freeman%2C%20attributing%20the%20reduction%20directly%20to%20a%20paucity%20of%20foreign%20visitors.%20Travelers%20from%20Japan%20and%20from%20China%2C%20two%20of%20America's%20top%20markets%20for%20incoming%20visits%2C%20have%20been%20slow%20to%20return%20to%20the%20US-with%20respective%20numbers%20%C2%A0currently%20at%20just%2037%25%20and%2037%25%20of%202019%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20political%20reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDomestic%20tourism%20remains%20the%20bright%20spot-leisure%20trips%20for%20Americans%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202023%20showed%20a%203%25%20increase%20over%202019%20levels%20and%20are%20projected%20to%20settle%20at%20those%20levels%20this%20year.%20Still%2C%20the%20US%20appears%20to%20face%20a%20larger%20reckoning%20that's%20affecting%20decisions%20by%20both%20domestic%20business%20visitors%20and%20international%20tourists.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20growing%20perception%20outside%20the%20USA%20that%20the%20country%20is%20no%20longer%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jack%20Ezon%2C%20founder%20of%20luxury%20boutique%20firm%20Embark%20Beyond%2C%20in%20his%20second-quarter%20Travel%20Trends%20Report.%20Higher%20crime%20rates%2C%20homelessness%20in%20cities%20and%20news%20of%20mass%20shootings%20are%20scaring%20potential%20visitors%2C%20the%20report%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20further%20states%20that%20Ezon's%20clients%20come%20%26quot%3Bwith%20a%20litany%20of%20restrictions%20removing%20places%20like%20Florida%2C%20Texas%20and%20Tennessee%20(among%20others)%20based%20on%20their%20draconian%20anti-LGBTQ%20or%20anti-abortion%20legislation.%20Others%20asking%20not%20to%20be%20exposed%20to%20destinations%20that%20are%20too%20'liberal.'%20Both%20are%20something%20we've%20not%20ever%20seen%20before.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStacy%20Ritter%2C%20CEO%20at%20Visit%20Lauderdale%2C%20which%20promotes%20tourism%20in%20the%20south%20of%20Florida%20from%20Miami-Dade%20to%20Palm%20Beach%20counties%2C%20echoes%20concerns%20that%20politics%20are%20impacting%20decisions%20to%20book%20events%20in%20her%20destination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20May%20to%20July%20this%20year%2C%20Visit%20Lauderdale%20received%2010%20cancellations%20for%20late%202023%2C%202024%20and%202026%20of%20group%20business%20events%20ranging%20in%20size%20from%20500%20to%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20attendees.%20The%20cancellations%20have%20already%20caused%20a%20loss%20of%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20room%20night%20bookings%2C%20the%20agency%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20I've%20seen%20a%20grouping%20in%20such%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time%20for%20political%20reasons.%20That's%20in%20excess%20of%20a%20%2420%20million%20economic%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ritter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlorida%20destinations%20such%20as%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20are%20experiencing%20event%20cancellations%2C%20and%20meeting%20planners%20cite%20politics%20as%20a%20cause.%20Photographer%3A%20Joe%20Raedle%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rivals%20conference%2C%20from%20radio%20personality%20Tom%20Joyner%2C%20celebrates%20students%20and%20alumni%20from%20historically%20Black%20colleges%20and%20universities.%20Set%20to%20take%20place%20in%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20this%20year%2C%20it%20was%20canceled%20on%20July%207.%20It%20would%20have%20brought%2010%2C000%20attendees%20over%20the%20three-day%20Labor%20Day%20weekend%20holiday%20to%20Broward%20County%2C%20Ritter%20says.%20The%20Chicago-based%20American%20Specialty%20Toy%20Retail%20Association%20was%20planning%20an%20event%20in%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20in%202026%20but%20reconsidered%2C%20citing%20the%20%26quot%3Bunfriendly%20political%20environment%20in%20Florida.%26quot%3B%20The%20group%20is%20now%20considering%20Milwaukee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20event%20bookings%20require%20more%20lead%20time%2C%20they%20are%20difficult%20to%20reschedule%2C%20so%20a%20slowdown%20now%20can%20wield%20a%20far%20greater%20impact%20later.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20now%20know%20that%20there%20are%20meeting%20and%20conference%20planners%20which%20aren't%20even%20sending%20requests%20for%20proposals%20to%20any%20of%20us%20in%20Florida%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ritter%2C%20noting%20that%20cancellations%20began%20trickling%20in%20during%20April%202022%2C%20after%20passage%20in%20Florida%20of%20the%20first%20so-called%20Don't%20Say%20Gay%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExact%20words%20from%20meeting%20planners%20for%20Humana%2C%20the%20Society%20for%20Maternal%20Fetal%20Medicine%20and%20American%20Crafts%20Spirits%20Association%2C%20she%20says%2C%20were%3A%20%26quot%3BFlorida%20is%20out%20now%20due%20to%20politics%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BFlorida%20is%20off%20the%20table%20right%20now%20due%20to%20policies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20South%20Florida%20tourism%20at%20least%2C%20%C2%A0she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20more%20a%20question%20of%20what%20are%20we%20not%20even%20able%20to%20bid%20for%20that%20we%20would%20normally%20have%20had%20an%20opportunity%20to%20bid%20for%3F%20I%20can't%20even%20quantify%20that.%26quot%3B%20The%20setbacks%20come%20amid%20a%20more%20than%20%241.5%20billion%20convention%20center%20expansion%20project%20that's%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVisit%20Orlando%20has%20suffered%20a%20similar%20round%20of%20cancelled%20meetings%2C%20CEO%20Casandra%20Matej%20confirmed%20in%20a%20recent%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJeremy%20Redfern%2C%20press%20secretary%20at%20the%20office%20of%20Governor%20Ron%20DeSantis%2C%20brushed%20aside%20such%20concerns.%20In%20an%20emailed%20statement%20to%20Bloomberg%2C%20he%20said%20that%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20Governor%20DeSantis%20announced%20in%20May%2C%20Florida%20is%20experiencing%20record%20tourism%2C%20with%20Q1%202023%20having%20the%20largest%20volume%20of%20visitors%20during%20a%20single%20quarter%20in%20recorded%20history.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERedfern%20pointed%20to%20a%20recent%20report%20that%20Florida%20is%20one%20of%20six%20fast-growing%20Southern%20states%20contributing%20more%20to%20the%20national%20gross%20domestic%20product%20than%20the%20Northeast%2C%20and%20cited%20a%20July%202023%20CNBC%20ranking%20of%20the%20Sunshine%20State%20as%20the%20nation's%20best%20component%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20US%20Travel's%20Freeman%2C%20the%20sluggish%20recovery%20of%20US%20travel%20has%20more%20to%20do%20with%20inefficiency%20than%20with%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20heard%20the%20politics%20comments%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20going%20back%20to%20the%20George%20W.%20Bush%20administration%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20US%20is%20still%20the%20most%20desired%20nation%20to%20visit%2C%20so%20you%20have%20to%20ask%20yourself%3A%20If%20they%20want%20to%20come%2C%20why%20aren't%20they%20coming%3F%20And%20I%20think%20that's%20a%20lot%20less%20about%20politics%20and%20it%20is%20a%20lot%20more%20about%20obstacles%20that%20are%20being%20put%20people's%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690461780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fnkk22sq8_us-generic-650_650x400_27_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-improves-visa-wait-times-for-indians-yet-to-recover-tourist-traffic-4245582%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22International%20tourist%20arrivals%20remain%20at%2026%25