rce%20would%20soon%20be%20larger%20than%20China%E2%80%99s.%20If%20the%20productive%20capacity%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20massive%20labour%20force%20is%20effectively%20harnessed%2C%20India%20could%20be%20on%20its%20way%20to%20become%20the%20new%20Asian%20giant.%20The%20Elephant%20would%20finally%20overtake%20the%20Dragon.%20Or%20would%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHowever%2C%20the%20story%20isn%E2%80%99t%20so%20straightforward.%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20bigger%20population%20size%20will%20not%20translate%20to%20a%20larger%20working%20age%20population%20for%20the%20country%20(vis-%C3%A0-vis%20China)%20immediately%20(Figure%201).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%201%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F16062023%2Ffigure1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3ELooks%20like%20your%20browser%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20iframes.%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20demographic%20cohort%20would%20be%20bigger%20than%20China%E2%80%99s%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20China%20will%20still%20have%20a%20bigger%20working%20age%20population%20(those%20aged%2015-64)%20for%20another%20two%20years.%20It%20is%20only%20in%202025%20that%20there%20will%20be%20more%20people%20aged%20between%2015-64%20in%20India%20(994.7%20million)%20than%20in%20China%20(987.4%20million).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20people%20in%20the%20working%20age%20group%20are%20in%20the%20labour%20force%2C%20which%20comprises%20employed%20individuals%20and%20those%20willing%20to%20work%20but%20not%20employed%20(i.e.%2C%20unemployed).%20For%20that%20we%20must%20look%20at%20the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%2C%20or%20LFPR.%20India%E2%80%99s%20LFPRs%20are%20not%20only%20much%20below%20the%20global%20average%2C%20but%20significantly%20lower%20than%20China%E2%80%99s.%20As%20of%202021%20(the%20latest%20year%20for%20which%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FSL.TLF.ACTI.ZS%5C%22%3Ecomparable%20data%20is%20available%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%2075.8%20percent%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20working%20age%20population%20(15-64)%20was%20part%20of%20its%20labour%20force%20i.e.%20they%20were%20either%20employed%2C%20or%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20data%20from%20the%20International%20Labour%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20(ILO)%20modelled%20estimates%20show.%20In%20India%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20only%2051.3%20percent%20of%20those%20in%20this%20age%20group%20were%20part%20of%20the%20labour%20force%20in%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%202%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F16062023%2Ffigure2.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3ELooks%20like%20your%20browser%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20iframes.%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20this%20difference%20is%20driven%20by%20the%20chasm%20between%20the%20female%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20in%20the%20two%20countries.%20India%20has%20lower%20rates%20of%20both%20male%20and%20female%20labour%20force%20participation%20compared%20to%20China%2C%20but%20the%20gap%20is%20much%20bigger%20for%20female%20LFPRs.%20In%202021%2C%2076.2%20percent%20of%20Indian%20men%20(15-64)%20were%20part%20of%20its%20labour%20force%2C%20and%20in%20China%20this%20share%20was%2080.5%20percent.%20In%20the%20same%20year%2C%20only%2024.6%20percent%20of%20women%20(15-64)%20were%20part%20of%20the%20labour%20force%20in%20India%2C%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%2070.8%20percent%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20difference%20in%20LFPR%20essentially%20means%20that%20in%202021%2C%20while%20there%20were%20986.5%20million%20people%20in%20China%20aged%2015-64%2C%20there%20were%20747.9%20million%20people%20who%20were%20employed%20or%20looking%20for%20employment%2C%20our%20calculations%20show.%20In%20India%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20there%20were%20950.2%20million%20people%20aged%2015-64%20in%202021%2C%20but%20only%20487.9%20million%20were%20part%20of%20the%20labour%20force%20(Figure%203).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20wider%20gap%20in%20FLFPR%2C%20this%20difference%20was%20starker%20for%20the%20female%20population%2C%20our%20calculations%20show.%20In%202021%2C%20China%20had%20an%20estimated%20478.3%20million%20women%20aged%2015-64%2C%20and%20its%20female%20labour%20force%20was%20an%20estimated%20338.6%20million%20in%20size.%20In%20India%2C%20the%20female%20labour%20force%20was%20only%20112.8%20million%20in%20comparison%20even%20though%20it%20had%20458.2%20million%20women%20in%20that%20age%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EFigure%203%3A%20Estimated%20working%20age%20(15-64%20years)%20population%20and%20labour%20force%2C%20India%20and%20China%2C%202021%20(in%20millions)%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Cthead%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Cth%3E%3C%2Fth%3E%5Cn%3Cth%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fth%3E%5Cn%3Cth%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fth%3E%5Cn%3Cth%3ERatio%20(China%2FIndia)%3C%2Fth%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fthead%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EPopulation%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E986.5%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E950.2%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E1.04%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3ELFPR%20(in%20percent)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E75.8%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E51.3%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5